# AKOS MKTOps Discipline

Use this rule whenever authoring or reviewing **campaign briefs**,
**creative assets**, **landing pages**, **adapter registries** (CRM /
EMAIL / COMMUNICATION / SCHEDULING / ATTRIBUTION), **funnel-stage
measurement plans**, or **persona-targeting metadata**. Codifies the
mechanical layer of
[`MKTOPS_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Marketing/canonicals/MKTOPS_DISCIPLINE.md)
(Wave M P5 mint per D-IH-86-BW).

## When this rule applies

- Author or modify a campaign brief, creative asset, or landing page
  spec under `docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Marketing/**`.
- Mint or modify an adapter registry row under any of the 5 MKTOps
  adapter registries (CRM / EMAIL / COMMUNICATION / SCHEDULING /
  ATTRIBUTION).
- Modify campaign metadata (`target_persona_ids`, `lifecycle_state`,
  UTM tagging) in any campaign artifact.
- Touch brand-canon-bound external-facing prose per
  `akos-brand-baseline-reality.mdc` + `akos-external-render-discipline.mdc`.

## RULE 1 â€” Campaign artefacts must satisfy the 7 MKTOps dimensions (binding)

Every campaign artefact (brief / creative / landing page / sequence)
must pass the 7 MKTOps dimensions defined in
[`MKTOPS_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Marketing/canonicals/MKTOPS_DISCIPLINE.md)
Â§2 before launch:

- **MKT-01** Campaign lifecycle quality â†’ all 5 lifecycle gates
  pass with operator approval
- **MKT-02** Funnel-stage UX â†’ UX bar inherited from
  `UX_DISCIPLINE.md` (UX-05 + UX-07) per stage class
- **MKT-03** Landing-page conversion â†’ Core Web Vitals + persona-
  class conversion benchmark
- **MKT-04** Attribution trail â†’ UTM consistency + adapter status
- **MKT-05** Channel coverage â†’ adapter registry `status: active`
  for all in-use adapters
- **MKT-06** Persona-fit â†’ â‰¥ 1 FK-resolved persona target per
  campaign
- **MKT-07** Brand-voice integrity â†’
  `validate_brand_baseline_reality_drift.py` PASS + brand-jargon-audit
  scan clean

Mechanical enforcement happens via adapter-registry validators +
brand-drift validator + planned `mktops_campaign_quality_check.py`
runbook (forward-chartered).

## RULE 2 â€” Adapter status metadata is load-bearing (binding)

Every adapter registry row carries a `status` column with the 5-value
enum per `akos-executable-process-catalog.mdc` Rule 2
(`active` / `inactive` / `planned` / `deprecated` / `experimental`).
MKTOps consumes this metadata: campaigns may only invoke `active`
adapters; `inactive` or `deprecated` invocations are a release-gate
FAIL.

When a new adapter is registered, the mint follows the Normalised
Adapter Pattern: paired canonical Pydantic model + paired registry
CSV + paired validator + paired test + paired release-gate wiring.

## RULE 3 â€” External-facing artefacts must pass brand-baseline-reality (binding)

Every external-facing campaign artefact (landing page body, email
body, ad creative copy, deck slide, dossier) must pass
`scripts/validate_brand_baseline_reality_drift.py` per
`akos-brand-baseline-reality.mdc` before publish. CORPINT-internal
register tokens are forbidden in external surfaces; translation to
external register is mandatory.

This rule is a sibling to MKT-07 (brand-voice integrity); the cursor
rule names the enforcement contract; the discipline canonical names
the multi-dimensional bar.

## When this rule does NOT apply

- Internal-only operator dashboards (J-OP audience only); inherit
  lighter brand-axis only.
- Operator scratchwork or session notes.
- Test fixtures.

